<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#E6EBD7" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post82583"></a>
	
	<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#333399"><b>Onetree Tallbarque</b></font><br>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#333399">TDG Supporter</font><br>
	<img src="avatar.php?userid=77&amp;dateline=1065118475" border="0" alt=""><p>
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#333399">Registered: Sep 2003<br>
	Location: Silicon Valley, CA<br>
	Posts: 241</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#E6EBD7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#333399"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#333399">Nuts.<br />
<br />
This is window dressing. After 4.5 years of playing this game I don't need font changes or dealy-bobs over critters' heads or red pulsing loincloths (for giants) to show their vitality, and I especially don't need to be barraged by 30 different pop-up tell windows at once, which would happen when I obtain something in a raid (/tell onetree Congrats!). If these changes go in I'm just going to turn them off.<br />
<br />
(1) Seasoned players need LDoN to deliver group and raid events truely tuned to <i>whatever</i> party makeup enters the fray, not have the burden placed on us with choices: normal (ie. easy) or hard (not worth the trouble). (2) Our melee compatriots need their balance concerns addressed sooner rather than later -- because they've suffered long enough. (3) We need SOE Customer Support to pursue buggy LDoN adventures to the developers and back, not just say, "We're sorry we can't do anything" and end it there -- I have first hand experience with this. (4) And long suffering tradeskillers need their special containers altered to support stacked components. I need it to help keep this very real c-t pain that's been developing in my right forearm over the last 4 years in abeyance.<br />
<br />
We're looking for substantive changes to keep our interest into the future, not this window dressing.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#333399">__________________<br>
