	<td bgcolor="#FCFAEE" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#333399"> <b>Re: Upcoming Updates for Oct/Nov 2003</b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#333399"><blockquote><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#333399">quote:</font><hr><i>Originally posted by Sylphan </i><br />
From EQLive...<br />
<br />
/tell windows - It is very easy to lose /tells in the confusion of combat. We want to add an option that would work much like an instant messenger. Each time you get a "tell" from a new character, a new chat window would open. That window will only display "tells" from the particular character, and any message sent from the chat window would automatically be sent as a "tell" to that character. Obviously this would be an optional feature. <hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
Why do this? I predict this feature will be turned off by a vast majority of the players -- in fact, turned off by so many that it's probably not even worth implementing. Could you imagine being griefed by people with tell bombs that completely cluttered your screen, particularly when in a raid or LDoN dungeon? What fun. /toggletellwindow off ... at least here.<br />
<br />
<blockquote><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#333399">quote:</font><hr>We are also working on removing one of the more tedious "features" of the game, the need to practice Sense Heading. <hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
Why not? It's not like, with PoP books and Nexus portals, the average newb needs to learn how to get around these days anyway. <img src="images/smilies/tongue.gif" border="0" alt=""><br />
<br />
<blockquote><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#333399">quote:</font><hr>Most folks have that skill mapped to trigger along with one of their movement keys. Not an exciting skill to practice. So we plan to have all characters start with a 200 skill in Sense Heading. This will allow new players to navigate more easily, and will reduce a bit of tedium over the course of gameplay. <hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
Then why not just get rid of the skill altogether? I also wonder if this will affect pre-existing characters, such as my mid-20's lowbies. <br />
<br />
<blockquote><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#333399">quote:</font><hr><br />
Some options being considered are:<br />
<br />
Improve melee damage-increasing disciplines <br />
Improve Planes of Power melee weapons<hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
Yea on the first one, a firm nay on the second. Balancing via equipment is a bad idea, IMHO, unless SOE'll be handing the "Class Fixing" equipment out to all characters of that class. <img src="images/smilies/rolleyes.gif" border="0" alt=""><br />
<br />
I'm just happy that they are taking the time to keep us informed. I was beginning to think that SOE had concluded that keeping us informed was worse off from a PR standpoint than just instituting changes with no advance notice.<br />
<br />
P.S. The Inn in North Ro now has a broken door, at least on my server. Get crackin'! <img src="images/smilies/tongue.gif" border="0" alt=""><br />
<br />
Aldane Aglond<br />
Ayonae Ro</font></p>
	
