	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#333399"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#333399"><blockquote><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#333399">quote:</font><hr>/tell windows - It is very easy to lose /tells in the confusion of combat. We want to add an option that would work much like an instant messenger. Each time you get a "tell" from a new character, a new chat window would open. That window will only display "tells" from the particular character, and any message sent from the chat window would automatically be sent as a "tell" to that character. Obviously this would be an optional feature. <hr></blockquote> <br />
<br />
You know, the more I think about it, this has a potential to be exploited.  Imagine two guilds fighting over a spawn.  They both know when it will pop, so Guild A gets everyone in the guild to send /tells to the key raiders (main tank, cleric rotation) in Guild B just moments before spawn.  Every cleric in Guild B has 50 /tell windows pop up at the same time and EQ crashes... I'm sure someone will try this.  And until everyone turns the feature off, it'll probably work <img src="images/smilies/frown.gif" border="0" alt=""></font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p></p>
